verbose_text: UBE2L3 protein levels were strongly elevated in Ki-67 + proliferating B cells (p < 0.0001) (XREF_FIG D) and also increased in CD95 + (Fas / APO-1) activated B cells (p < 0.0001) (XREF_FIG E), consistent with a role for UBE2L3 regulated NF-kappaB activation in both B cell proliferation and activation.
